,\"text\":\"**Following reflection rules**\\n\\nThe rule is clear: I shouldn't use reflection directly unless the public API requires it naturally. I considered whether Ant's public `Project` has a `setProperty` method, but that doesn't seem viable. Alternatively, I could use `RmicAdapterFactory.getRmic(SunRmic.class.getName(), task)` to resolve via `Class.forName` and `newInstance`, though it won't help with the active class's class$.\\n\\nI really need to cover the active class's synthetic class$ method since it isn't part of the public API.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about dynamic class loading in a native image context. It seems like Native Image has a closed world, which makes using URLClassLoader tricky since it can’t load new classes at runtime. Without the JVM, I suspect this isn't allowed. So, it might not be suitable for what I want to achieve. I could consider using a custom classloader to load classes from byte arrays, which I could include as resources instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring dynamic class definitions**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether defining a dynamic class is possible, and it seems unlikely. We could rely on a standard JVM instead of native, but that means tests must still run natively. Maybe we can utilize an existing active class from the application image? However, resetting without reflection or unsafe operations doesn’t seem feasible. I wonder if the test code can apply `org.apache.tools.ant.util.ReflectUtil` instead. Let's search that option further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_z6gBAnaYPOyUn6YOKbyluke5|fc_010f4918e2c38b170169f004991280819fb5d937e5495fa7e2", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"class Reflect|ReflectUtil|setAccessible|Field\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/ant/ant/1.6/main/extracted/main/org/apache/tools/ant tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant | head -100